problem בכל שהוא? במינו. שלא במינו בנותן טעם. shelo b'mino b'noten ta'am.

1079
00:54:36,060 --> 00:54:38,000
שלא במינו shelo b'mino it's נותן טעם. noten ta'am. So I should

1080
00:54:38,000 --> 00:54:40,800
say the one thing not discussed here is חמץ, chametz there actually

1081
00:54:40,800 --> 00:54:43,160
is an opinion in the ראשונים Rishonim that חמץ chametz is נותן

1082
00:54:43,160 --> 00:54:46,740
טעם. noten ta'am. Isn't that shocking? We go so crazy by פסח,

1083
00:54:46,340 --> 00:54:49,280
Pesach, even trace amounts or whatever. There actually is an opinion in

1084
00:54:49,280 --> 00:54:51,300
the ראשונים Rishonim that חמץ chametz is נותן טעם, noten ta'am, but

1085
00:54:51,300 --> 00:54:53,560
anyway the way we rule is that חמץ is more מחמיר machmir

1086
00:54:53,560 --> 00:54:58,440
than everything, that we would—a normal מחמיר machmir rule by חמץ would

1087
00:54:58,440 --> 00:55:01,160
be במינו בכל שהוא. b'mino b'kol shehu. But because of all the

1088
00:55:01,160 --> 00:55:06,052
חומרות *chumras* of פסח *Pesach* and because we generally don't treat חמץ

1089
00:55:06,052 --> 00:55:08,160
*chametz* as a דבר אסור *davar assur*, so we're super strict in

1090
00:55:08,160 --> 00:55:10,856
the other direction, so even by אינו מינו *eino mino* we go

1091
00:55:10,856 --> 00:55:12,680
בכל שהוא *b'chol shehu*. That's if it's a mixture that occurs on

1092
00:55:12,680 --> 00:55:15,620
פסח *Pesach*. A mixture that occurs before פסח *Pesach* would follow the

1093
00:55:15,620 --> 00:55:19,832
normal rule. What about קטניות *kitniyos*? קטניות *kitniyos* are technically even בטל

1094
00:55:19,832 --> 00:55:21,920
ברוב *batel b'rov*, but I'm not going to talk about practical aspects

1095
00:55:21,920 --> 00:55:24,892
of קטניות *kitniyos*. But last thing I'll say is that תוספות *Tosafos*

1096
00:55:24,892 --> 00:55:27,060
asks a question: why does the גמרא *Gemara* give the reason that

1097
00:55:27,060 --> 00:55:30,440
טבל *tevel* isn't בטל *batel* because of כהיתרו כך איסורו *k'heteiro kach

1098
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:33,040
issuro*? It should have said טבל *tevel* isn't בטל *batel* because it's

1099
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:35,400
the principle of דבר שיש לו מתירין *davar sheyesh lo matirin*. There's

1100
00:55:35,400 --> 00:55:38,640
another principle that things that you have a way that will be

1101
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:41,112
מותר *mutter* in some other way, we're not going to allow ביטול

1102
00:55:41,112 --> 00:55:43,552
*bittul* to make them מותר *mutter*. So if it's like a מוקצה

1103
00:55:43,552 --> 00:55:46,000
*muktzah* problem, just wait until after שבת *Shabbos*. If you could fix

1104
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:49,060
the טבל *tevel*, we're not going to allow the ביטול *bittul* to

1105
00:55:49,060 --> 00:55:50,752
make it מותר *mutter*. Make it מותר *mutter* the other way. So

1106
00:55:50,752 --> 00:55:54,156
תוספות *Tosafos* says and that's not בטל *batel* even בכל שהוא *b'chol

1107
00:55:54,156 --> 00:55:56,380
shehu*. So תוספות *Tosafos* asks why the גמרא *Gemara* gave this answer,

1108
00:55:56,380 --> 00:55:59,380
it could have given a different answer, and I'll just tell you

1109
00:55:59,380 --> 00:56:03,480
the one sentence easiest explanation is that the idea that we rule

1110
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:05,800
דבר שיש לו מתירין *davar sheyesh lo matirin* is not בטל *batel*

1111
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:10,860
is really one opinion of תנאים *Tannaim*. It's not the סתם *stam*

1112
00:56:10,860 --> 00:56:13,920
opinion. So it's not surprising that the גמרא *Gemara* wanted to give

1113
00:56:13,920 --> 00:56:17,320
a more general explanation rather than דבר שיש לו מתירין *davar sheyesh

1114
00:56:17,320 --> 00:56:19,812
lo matirin*, which is actually somewhat of a debate—we do rule it

1115
00:56:19,812 --> 00:56:22,480
למעשה *l'maiseh*, but at least in the גמרא *Gemara* it's somewhat of

1116
00:56:22,480 --> 00:56:25,640
a debated principle. Okay, so you got here a really nice primer

1117
00:56:25,640 --> 00:56:28,860
into ביטול *bittul*. This is a very fascinating area in the few

1118
00:56:28,860 --> 00:56:31,400
places that we say מין במינו לא בטל *min b'mino lo batel*.

1119
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:33,200
What do you say if it's מין במינו ואינו מינו *min b'mino

1120
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:36,852
v'eino mino*? This is a fascinating and important principle, not in רבי

1121
00:56:36,852 --> 00:56:38,920
יוחנן *Rebbi Yochanan*'s case, because רבי יוחנן *Rebbi Yochanan* was somehow assuming

1122
00:56:38,920 --> 00:56:42,980
that wine and wine could be בטל *batel*, which seems completely bizarre.

1123
00:56:42,980 --> 00:56:45,560
But in cases where you do have ביטול *bittul*, like if this

1124
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:48,200
is a little טריף *traif* chicken soup falling in drop by drop

1125
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:51,540
or חזיר *chazir* soup, even though the initial drops are בטל *batel*,

1126
00:56:51,540 --> 00:56:55,340
would you have to reassess the ביטול *bittul* when the proportions change?

1127
00:56:55,340 --> 00:56:58,160
And that's a very important question. Do you say חוזר וניעור *chozer

1128
00:56:58,160 --> 00:57:01,800
v'neiar* that you have to reassess it when the proportions change? Okay,

1129
00:57:01,800 --> 00:57:05,840
and then finally the whole discussion about which in general we rule

1130
00:57:05,840 --> 00:57:09,152
מין במינו *min b'mino* is בטל *batel* בשישים *b'shishim*, actually technically ברוב

1131
00:57:09,152 --> 00:57:12,232
*b'rov*, except for one or two exceptions. But there is a מחמיר

1132
00:57:12,232 --> 00:57:14,860
*machmir* position out there, which even רש"י *Rashi* פוסקנס *paskens* like, that

1133
00:57:14,860 --> 00:57:16,740
even בכל התורה כולה *b'chol hatorah kulo* מין במינו *min b'mino* is

1134
00:57:16,740 --> 00:57:19,064
בכל שהוא *b'chol shehu*. So good thing we don't פוסק *pasken* that

1135
00:57:19,064 --> 00:57:21,080
way. Okay, to be continued tomorrow.
